Lonely sadness<br/><br/>When I was sad,
<br />I like to bow my head and walk, focus on the ground in front of my shoes, it makes me feel like the world is so small that only I lived on it, sadness are everywhere;
<br />When I was sad,
<br />I like to stay in the house, lean on my bed, look at my little hope sadly, watching him bites my shoes hard and stubbornly, leave tears flood on my face;
<br />When I was sad,
<br />I like to recall the memory, sitting at the table with pen in my hand, but no any single word will be written, it seems like the sorrow is so thick that it blocks the spring of my creativity, the inspirations all died.
<br />When I was sad,
<br />I like to be cared, like a dog, stay in master's arms quietly, feel the gentle touch of master's soft hands on the head, and so down for the feeling of being loved.
<br />When I was sad,
<br />I like to keep silent, just be quiet, lean or lay down, even stay in the bed for a whole day, neither move nor eat, neither listen nor look, just don't want to be bothered by anything;   
<br />When I was sad,
<br />I like to buy snacks, like a mouse, take all my favorite food back home, choose whatever I like, eat as much as I want, no one can stop me;
<br />When I was sad,
<br />I like to watch a movie, the sadness will fade away while I was watching it, till I played the role totally, i will laugh or cry, fall asleep afterwards, never gonna wake up; 
<br /><br />---In fact, we should be alone when we were sad; and when you were sad, remember to love yourself more or even spoil yourself a little bit.
